<para>
  <link
  linkend="RegisteredClass-ColorMap"><classname>ColorMaps</classname></link>
  translate numbers into colors, for use in contour plots.
  <classname>SpectralMap</classname> maps colors in spectral order
  (blue-green-yellow-orange-red, from low to high values).
</para>
<para>
  The <varname>saturation</varname> and <varname>value</varname>
  parameters determine the fixed <link
  linkend="RegisteredClass-HSVColor">saturation</link> and <link
  linkend="RegisteredClass-HSVColor">value</link> of all the colors in
  the map.
</para>
<figure id="Figure-Spectral">
  <title>The Spectral Color Map</title>
  <mediaobject>
    <imageobject>
	  <imagedata fileref="FIGURES/colormaps/spectral.png"
	             format="PNG"/>
    </imageobject>
    <caption>
	  <para>
        Three versions of the spectral color map with different
        parameters.  High values are on top.  (a) The default values,
        <varname>saturation</varname>=<userinput>1</userinput> and
        <varname>value</varname>=<userinput>1.0</userinput>. (b)
        <varname>saturation</varname>=<userinput>0.5</userinput> and
        <varname>value</varname>=<userinput>1.0</userinput>. (c)
        <varname>saturation</varname>=<userinput>1.0</userinput> and
        <varname>value</varname>=<userinput>0.5</userinput>.
	  </para>
    </caption>
  </mediaobject>
</figure>

